    • Constructor Detail

      • DBGraph

        public DBGraph(DNAString[] reads,
               java.util.Map<DNAString,java.lang.Integer> kmers,
               int k,
               boolean verbose)
        Create new de Bruijn Graph (DBGraph) object from an array of DNAString reads for a given k-mer length k.

        The graph is created in 3 steps: (1) unique k-mers are counted in the set of reads and turned into new DBGNodes (2) nodes are connected based on k-1 overlap of their sequences (3) node multiplicities are computed by iterating over the read array

        Parameters:
        reads - array of DNAString reads.
        kmers - LinkedHashSet mapping k-mers to counts.
        k - k-mer size for creating this new graph.
        verbose - be verbose.

      • getAdjustedCovData

        public SimpleVec getAdjustedCovData()
        Produces a SimpleVec vector holding all coverage values of nodes in this graph adjusted by node sizes.

        For every DBGNode n in this graph, this methods adds n.getSize() entries containing its average coverage to the output array.

        Returns:
        node coverages amplified by node size.

      • removeBubbles

        public boolean removeBubbles(boolean verbose)
        Remove bubbles from the graph.

        This method removes bubbles which consist of a short non-branching path from a source node s to a target node t and a second potentially nonlinear path from s to t. The algorithm creates a set of linear candidate paths and calls findAndCutBubble on each of them.

        Parameters:
        verbose - be verbose
        Returns:
        true, if bubbles were resolved, false otherwise.

      • removeTips

        public boolean removeTips(boolean verbose)
        Remove tips from the graph.

        A node-twin pair with only one outgoing edge is considered an erroneous tip if its sequence is shorter than 2k and there exists an edge going from a junction to the graph with higher multiplicity than the edge going from the junction to the tip.

        Parameters:
        verbose - be verbose.
        Returns:
        true if nodes were removed, false otherwise.

      • simplify

        public void simplify(boolean correctErrors,

                     boolean verbose)
        Simplifies the graph by repeatedly applying removeTips, removeBubbles, removeLowCoverageBlocks and collapse.
        Parameters:

        cutoffCov - cutoff threshold for removeLowCoverageBlocks.
